# Inertia + Vue 3 Frontend Rules

## CRITICAL: inertia-app.js setup() — NEVER CHANGE THIS PATTERN

File: `resources/js/inertia-app.js`

The `setup()` callback in `createInertiaApp` MUST use `h(App, props)`:

```js
// ✅ CORRECT — always use this form
setup({ el, App, props, plugin }) {
    createApp({ render: () => h(App, props) }).use(plugin).mount(el);
}
```

```js
// ❌ WRONG — never use this form, even though it looks valid
setup({ el, App, props, plugin }) {
    createApp(App).use(plugin).mount(el);
}
```

### Why this matters

`@inertiajs/vue3` v1.x passes `initialPage` and `resolveComponent` through `props`.
Without `h(App, props)`, the Inertia `App` component receives no `initialPage`.
`router.init()` is then called with `initialPage = undefined`, and any Inertia
page throws:

```
TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'url')
    at Ql.handleInitialPageVisit
```

This produces a **blank screen** with no obvious cause. See `docs/CriticalFixProcedures.md` FIX-001.

### If you need to modify inertia-app.js

1. Read `docs/CriticalFixProcedures.md` FIX-001 first.
2. Do NOT change the `setup()` function signature or body.
3. `h` must always be imported from `vue`.
4. After any change, run `npm run build` and verify the page loads.

## Adding New Inertia Pages

All Vue page components go in `resources/js/Pages/` following the structure:
- `Pages/Admin/SomePage.vue` → `Inertia::render('Admin/SomePage')`
- `Pages/Billing/SomePage.vue` → `Inertia::render('Billing/SomePage')`

The glob `import.meta.glob('./Pages/**/*.vue')` auto-discovers all pages.
No changes to `inertia-app.js` are needed when adding new pages.

## Inertia vs Blade

- Inertia routes → `app.blade.php` (has `@inertia` directive, loads `inertia-app.js`)
- Blade routes → `admin.layouts.main` (Bootstrap/jQuery, loads `app.js`)
- **Never load `inertia-app.js` on a Blade page** — it will crash because there is no `#app[data-page]` element.
